The President released a statement on the observance of Diwali, highlighting its significance for Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and Buddhists. He mentioned that the festival reaffirms the importance of simple pleasures, spending time with loved ones, and performing service to others. The President also emphasized that light will triumph over darkness. He expressed pride in the diversity of faiths and traditions in the United States and mentioned the first-ever celebration of Diwali on Capitol Hill, where Democrats and Republicans came together. The President and Michelle Obama have had the opportunity to observe Diwali both at the White House and in India, and they wished everyone celebrating a Happy Diwali and Saal Mubarak (Happy New Year).